<br>
I believe the concensus was that both claims were false.  If Lucy is to believed, Planeswalk only increases movement speed by 125%, which is well less than Selos and less than speedcap.<br>
<br>
Based this thread<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallfrm8.showMessage?topicID=71.topic">p201.ezboard.com/ftheconc...D=71.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
The (pre-FoF) movement cap is somewhere between an increase of 156% and 169%, which Selo's hits with drums of the beast around level 50.  It is approximately 75.8 locs/second.  I believe the testing done for Reed's spreadsheet came up with a similar value of just over 160% increase, although I cannot open Reed's spreadsheet here.<br>
<br>
If you do not believe Lucy's figures (which is fairly reasoanble) it should be possible for a monk to verify that they are only going about 66 locs/second rather than about 76 l/s with planeswalk activated.<br>
<br>
Still, Planeswalk sounds quite nice.  It compares favorably to Flight of Eagles, and even Spirit of Cheetah.<br>
