<br>
As a bard who pulls raids consistantly, xp groups, hard ldons, ect ect, I find that my use of fade has dropped down to near nil in those enviornments for pulling.  When you understand mob pathing, mez/lullability, and what your group/raid is capable of - fade just isn't needed when you reach a certian skill level of pulling.  If we didn't have fade and still had all the tools available at our disposal, if you screwed up you would just die, get dragged, rez and go back out.  The only difference is 2-3 minutes of looting/rebuffing.<br>
<br>
