<br>
Worn items from Time and GoD zones have effects where they mitigate a % of spell damage. A common example is the Glyphed Prayer Ring. It has Spell Shield: +5% on it. What that means is any time you are hit by a instant duration detrimental spell (a DD) 5% of that spell damage does not hit you. It even gets rid of damage from non-resistable spells.<br>
<br>
So for example if you were fighting MB in PoI and a spider got threw a 3K non-resistable AE DD goes off. If you had a Spell Shield: +5% item you would only get hit for 95% of the spell damage (2895hps).<br>
<br>
DoT Shield and Spell Shield stack with themselves. So if you had Spell Shield: 5% on one item and Spell Shield: +3% on another item you would be hit by only 92% of a spell's damage. Same thing with DoT Shielding.<br>
<br>
Now that many spells in GoD (and Elementals/Time to some degree) are very hard to resist at 500 to all resists bards have lost the utility of one of our primary rolls. The addition of a shielding (not rune) effect would return some of our utility and importance to a raid.<br>
<br>
